        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_46333425" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="5" data-reason="Interesting">
            <div class="comment-body">Madoff is an excellent example of why handing your money to an individual or small group (just like the ameteurs at Mt. Gox) to keep in your trust is an awful idea. Real banks, the ones with experience not losing all of your money or that are regulated and insured by the U.S. gov't, by comparison, are stable, secure, and at least reliable enough for an economy to run on.</div>
