    <div id="comment_46333235">
        <header data-points="4" data-reason="Interesting">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Mt.Gox has a long history of problems, Bitcoin not"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Mt.Gox has a long history of problems, Bitcoin not<span> (4, Interesting)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~JcMorin" class="author" title="author name and user ID">JcMorin (930466) </a> | about 5 months ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=4831793&cid=46333235">(#46333235)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_46333235" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="4" data-reason="Interesting">
            <div class="comment-body">Mt.Gox is like a bank, it's not because one big bank fail (Lehman Brothers for instance) that the whole currency is bad. Mt Gox was poorly managed, bad software code, bad PR, often DDOS. They couldn't stand the #1 place they hold for too long. I'm very sorry for everyone who lost money with Mt. Gox but don't get me wrong. Bitcoin ecosystem still exist and many other exchanges services will emerge as of that. Users and investors will have to be very careful about where they hold their money. In my case, I trust my on own encrypted devices.</div>
